# File and directory placement

## Component directory

```
ComponentName/
  atoms/
  molecules/                  ← each child has its own hook
  hooks/                      ← focused hooks (one per directory)
  utils/
  ComponentName.component.tsx
  useComponentName.hook.ts
  ComponentName.context.tsx   ← sibling coordination only (see Context rule)
  ComponentName.types.ts
  ComponentName.constants.ts
  index.ts
```

## Feature page with multiple sections

When a page has map + header + sheet + overlay (or similar), **do not** use one `usePageContent.hook.ts` at the root. Instead:

```
FeaturePageContent/
  FeaturePageContent.component.tsx
  FeaturePageContentV2.context.tsx       ← Provider + narrow context
  hooks/
    useFeaturePageContentV2State/      ← coordination state for Provider
    useFeaturePageContentV2Context/    ← consumer hook
    useFeaturePageContentV2Mount/      ← mount ref only (optional)
  molecules/
    FeatureV2MapLayer/
      FeatureV2MapLayer.component.tsx
      useFeatureV2MapLayer.hook.ts
    FeatureV2BottomSheet/
      ...
```

## Standalone hook directory

```
useSomething/
  useSomething.hook.ts
  useSomething.types.ts
  useSomething.constants.ts
  index.ts
```

## Utility placement
- Cross-feature → `src/utils/<name>/`
- Feature-specific → `<Feature>/utils/<name>/`
- One util per directory; never duplicate a global util locally.

## Types and constants
- Types → `.types.ts`. Constants → `.constants.ts`. No magic numbers in logic files.
- Closed string sets (statuses, filters, modes): define `FOO_STATUSES` + `FOO_STATUS` once, derive the type, and reuse in switches/UI/API — see root `status-and-enum-constants.mdc`.


## Exports, naming, tests
- Export through `index.ts`. Exact suffixes: `.component.tsx`, `.hook.ts`, `.util.ts`, `.types.ts`, `.constants.ts`, `.context.tsx`.
- Create a matching test when you create a hook, util, or component.

## Context rule

Create `ComponentName.context.tsx` when siblings need shared state — **not** as a dump for all feature logic.

**Context value should contain:**
- Refs/handlers shared between siblings (sheet ref, `openSheet`, viewport, coordination callbacks)
- Mode flags siblings need (`showCityPicker`)

**Context value must NOT contain:**
- All derived UI for every child (`mapPlaces`, `filteredCities`, `selectedPlace`, loading overlays, i18n `t`)
- Everything a god hook would have returned

If removing one molecule would force editing a 100+ line state hook, the boundaries are wrong — move derived data into that molecule's hook.

See `feature-composition.mdc` and `hook-files.mdc`.
